Oh, I by no means agree with the elimination of biological sex as a reality. I think it can co-exist with the definition/re-definition of gender. I think biological sex has significant implications that shouldn’t be overridden, especially when it comes to law and things like restrooms, etc. I just think that gender is a different classification. I don’t agree that trans-women should be allowed to go into a woman’s restroom that’s based on sex. I think there should be other options for trans individuals or at least a stronger emphasis on gender neutral bathrooms alongside the sex separated ones. Of course, this is completely up to the property owner to implement and many do already have private stalls for people of all sexes and genders. It’s important to keep the notion of biological sex alive while also maintaining inclusiveness for those who may identify differently. A man is a man and a woman is a woman at birth, but if a dude feels more comfortable dressing and acting like a woman he has the right to do so, but his or her choice should not override basic genetics.
